<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world]]></title><link/> https://www.wsj.com/news/world <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/wsj/en-us/world" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 8 月 9 日星期三 20:03:02 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Haitian Kidnappers Release U.S. Nurse and Her Daughter]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>西半球最贫穷的国家正在应对一波犯罪团伙暴力和绑架浪潮<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122473"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="645" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832829?width=860&amp;height=645" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">阿利克斯·多塞维尔 (Alix Dorsainvil) 与丈夫桑德罗·多塞维尔 (Sandro Dorsainvil) 上个月被绑架。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：El Roi/法新社/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122473"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jose-decordoba" itemprop="url" rel="author">何塞·德·科尔多瓦</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 9 日下午 3:15 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/haitian-kidnappers-release-u-s-nurse-and-her-daughter-24311263"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>一名美国护士和她年幼的女儿周三在海地被绑架者释放，她们被囚禁了近两周，是西半球最贫穷国家不断增加的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/gangs-threaten-to-tip-haiti-into-a-failed-state-11634654955?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">绑架和杀戮</a>事件的受害者。</p><p> El Roi Haiti 在首都太子港附近为大约 400 名儿童开办了一所学校，该组织表示，该组织主任的妻子阿利克斯·多塞维尔 (Alix Dorsainvil) 和他们的女儿于 7 月 27 日被绑架。</p><p>海地国王在一份声明中表示：“在这种情况下，仍有很多事情需要处理和治愈。”该组织表示，他们的获释带来了“感激和极度的喜悦”。没有透露其他细节，包括是否支付了赎金。</p><p>海地王要求不要尝试联系 Dorsainvil 或她的家人。</p><p>自两年前海地总统若弗内尔·莫伊兹被暗杀以来，海地一直陷入社会动荡和犯罪团伙暴力的漩涡之中。 2021 年 7 月，20 多名前哥伦比亚士兵冲进总统府，莫伊兹被杀，他的妻子受伤。</p><p>海地<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-arrests-florida-businessmen-accused-of-plotting-haiti-presidents-killing-cd21ce08?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对暗杀事件的调查</a>陷入僵局，最初有 40 多人被拘留。美国检察官在迈阿密取得了进展，其中一人已承认杀人罪，另有 10 人在联邦法院面临指控。</p><p>暗杀事件发生后，绑架和杀戮事件急剧增加，因为许多强大的团伙与腐败的政客和商人有联系，为争夺太子港的控制权而战。</p><p>在本周的一份报告中，联合国儿童基金会记录了今年迄今为止近 300 起绑架妇女和儿童的案件，与 2022 年全年的数量大致相同，是 2021 年的三倍。</p><p>联合国儿童基金会拉丁美洲和加勒比地区主任加里·科尼尔表示：“绑架和诱拐事件不断增长的趋势极其令人担忧。”</p><p>联合国儿童基金会表示，海地安全和经济的恶化已使约 520 万人（其中包括 300 万儿童）面临危险，该国人口约一半处于危险之中。</p><p>该校表示，多尔塞维尔来自新罕布什尔州，自 2020 年以来一直在海地国王医院担任学校护士，并于 2021 年与该组织的主任结婚。她第一次来到海地是在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748703798904575069614263432520?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">2010 年地震</a>之后，据估计，这场地震已造成超过 20 万人死亡。</p><p>上个月，在多尔塞维尔被绑架的同一天，美国大使馆下令所有非紧急人员离开该国。</p><p>海地追踪绑架事件的组织人权分析与研究中心表示，自 1 月份以来，该国已发生 539 起绑架事件，其中至少有 51 名外国人。</p><p>该中心表示：“这种情况表明第三季度暴力和其他帮派活动有所增加。”</p><p>去年，海地总理阿里尔·亨利</p>要求联合国和国际社会<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-n-considers-sanctions-international-mission-to-restore-security-in-haiti-11666199198?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">派遣一支安全部队，</a>帮助装备和人员均处于劣势的海地警察镇压该国的暴力团伙。一些分析人士称，这些团伙控制着首都约80%的地区，并正在将其势力范围扩展到该国的农村地区。<p></p><p>美国和加拿大一直不愿意率领这样的任务，但上个月肯尼亚政府表示愿意这样做，并将派遣多达 1,000 名肯尼亚警察协助海地警察。肯尼亚表示将在八月中旬之前向海地派遣考察团。巴哈马已同意派遣约 150 名军官。</p><p>美国国务卿安东尼·布林肯表示，美国将推动联合国安理会通过决议，授权向海地派遣多国部队。</p><p> 2021年10月，17名美国和加拿大传教士被绑架，其中包括4名儿童和1名8个月大的婴儿， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/haiti-missionaries-kidnapping-11634584227?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">引起了全世界的关注</a>。传教士在接下来的两个月内被释放。绑匪要求每名俘虏支付 100 万美元的赎金，但尚不清楚是否支付了赎金。</p><p>写信给何塞·德·科尔多瓦： <a href="mailto:jose.decordoba@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jose.decordoba@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 19:15:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/haitian-kidnappers-release-us-nurse-and-her-daughter-24311263</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/haitian-kidnappers-release-us-nurse-and-her-daughter-24311263<author><![CDATA[José de Córdoba]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>帮派</category><category>绑架/劫持</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>帮派</category><category>绑架</category><category>绑架</category><category>犯罪企业</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Canada Says China Likely Behind Disinformation-Campaign Targeting Lawmaker]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>对中国干涉的指控促使政府承诺提高警惕<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122173"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832721?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">保守党议员迈克尔·庄（上图为 2017 年）呼吁对北京采取强硬路线。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：克里斯·瓦蒂/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001122173"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/paul-vieira" itemprop="url" rel="author">保罗·维埃拉</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 9 日下午 2:15 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-says-china-likely-behind-disinformation-campaign-targeting-lawmaker-22fad088"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>加拿大周三表示，中国“极有可能”在 5 月份帮助策划了一场针对保守党议员的网上虚假信息运动，随着官员们加大力度发现和阻止他们所说的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-confronts-allegations-of-china-led-electoral-interference-30f374f1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国对加拿大政治的干预</a>。</p><p>加拿大外交部表示，这一所谓的活动于 5 月在中国通讯应用程序<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TCEHY" class="">微信</a>上展开<span class="company-name-type">，</span>历时 10 多天，目标是保守党议员 Michael Chong。庄在2021年促使加拿大立法机构正式宣布<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-n-human-rights-agency-issues-report-on-xinjiang-over-chinas-protest-11661986730?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">北京对待维吾尔族穆斯林少数民族的方式为</a>种族灭绝方面发挥了重要作用，他还多次批评现任自由党政府未能对北京采取更强硬的立场。</p><p>加拿大表示，微信上的大部分活动都集中在“传播有关张的身份的虚假叙述，包括有关他的背景、政治立场和家族传统的评论和主张”。加拿大外交部补充说，没有迹象表明张或其家人面临任何安全威胁。</p><p>加拿大表示，“中国极有可能在信息行动中发挥了作用”。官员们表示，发布有关 Chong 材料的消息来源中有三分之一包括官方媒体机构和账户，“可能与中国国家机器有关，但其联系可能不透明”，并补充说，他们估计全球有 2 至 500 万微信用户查看了内容。</p><p>外交部表示：“加拿大永远不会接受对我们民主或内政的任何形式的干涉。”并补充说，它打算向中国外交官表达其对微信活动的担忧。</p><p>中国驻渥太华大使馆的代表没有立即回应置评请求。微信母公司、中国腾讯控股的发言人没有回应置评请求。</p><p>加拿大在调查结果中表示，针对 Chong 的活动“可能违反了微信的用户行为准则”，但他们没有发现任何迹象表明微信试图应用其内容审核标准。</p><p>加拿大官员今年 5 月向 Chong 透露了最初于 2021 年流传的情报报告，该报告显示一名中国驻多伦多外交官要求中国官员追踪并可能恐吓 Chong 在香港的亲属。庄先生通报情况后不久， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-expels-chinese-diplomat-following-threat-to-conservative-lawmaker-939aaaa5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">该外交官就被驱逐了</a>。一名加拿大安全官员告诉立法者，总理和内阁其他部长都没有被告知张的亲属面临的安全风险。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>有关中国政府干涉加拿大政治的指控激怒了总理贾斯汀·特鲁多的自由党政府，</p>自 2015 年上台以来，他在选民中的支持率接近历史最低水平。加拿大安全官员告诉这位保守党前领导人，北京曾试图阻止保守党在 2021 年大选中推翻特鲁多领导的自由党。 。<p></p><p>中国一再否认有关国内干涉的指控，称这些指控“毫无根据”。</p><p>特鲁多最初试图淡化对所谓中国活动的担忧，称官员已向他保证 2021 年选举将公平进行。六月，他承诺与反对党合作成立一个委员会，可能由一名法官领导，进行调查。这些会谈仍在继续。</p><p>庄表示，最新信息进一步证明了所谓的中国针对加拿大政治的攻击，他呼吁特鲁多政府启动正式调查，建立外国代理人登记册，并撤换北京任命的其他驻加拿大外交官。</p><p> “显然，必须采取更多措施来打击来自北京的外国干涉，”庄说。</p><p>写信给保罗·维埃拉 (Paul Vieira)： <a href="mailto:Paul.Vieira@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Paul.Vieira@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:15:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-says-china-likely-behind-disinformation-campaign-targeting-lawmaker-22fad088</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-says-china-likely-behind-disinformation-campaign-targeting-lawmaker-22fad088<author><![CDATA[Paul Vieira]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S., Allies Could Counter China’s Economic Coercion—If They Unite]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>新研究表明，各国对中国数百种关键产品的集体出口具有潜在影响力<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121782"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="574" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832640?width=860&amp;height=574" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">中国进口太阳能电池板所需的银粉主要来自日本、美国和韩国。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：str/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121782"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/timothy-w-martin" itemprop="url" rel="author">蒂莫西·W·马丁</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 9 日下午 1:58 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-allies-could-counter-chinas-economic-coercionif-they-unite-c45d2f8d"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>最新研究表明，美国及其盟国的协调行动可能会损害中国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/canada-calls-china-disruptive-global-actor-11669579816?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">将经济痛苦</a>作为政治报复的能力，但这需要采取前所未有的集体行动来对付世界第二大经济体。</p><p>中国长期以来一直<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-pressure-tactics-against-other-countries-largely-ineffective-study-finds-3f49561f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">利用经济胁迫手段</a>对政治上与北京有分歧的国家进行惩罚。中国试图通过一系列产品和行业——从挪威三文鱼、 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-signals-readiness-to-further-ease-trade-dispute-with-australia-93dc97a7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">澳大利亚葡萄酒</a>到<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-antimissile-system-in-south-korea-a-source-of-chinese-anger-cleared-for-full-deployment-8141b4dc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">韩国团体旅游——</a>对被视为轻视的行为进行报复。</p><p>北京否认使用贸易作为武器。它还指责华盛顿才是真正的罪犯，并以<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">美国限制对华科技出口</a>为例。</p><p>被中国针对的国家经常发现自己陷入了一场无法获胜的一对一摊牌之中。其他努力，从<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/nations-aim-to-secure-supply-chains-by-turning-offshoring-into-friend-shoring-11652612580?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">降低风险到友商支持</a>，都采取了更为间接的解决方案，即创建绕过北京的替代供应链。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="1200" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832291?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>另一种选择：美国和其他志同道合的国家可以集体将与中国的贸易武器化。这样做将让北京付出明显而直接的代价。</p><p>根据战略与战略研究中心的 Victor D. Cha 对 2022 年全球贸易数据的分析，中国对从美国及其盟国进口的约 412 种商品的依赖度至少达到 70%，每年价值约 470 亿美元。国际研究，一个总部位于华盛顿的智囊团。产品范围从奢侈品到中国主要工业所需的原材料。对于许多产品，北京缺乏现成的本土替代品。</p><p>分析称，中国进口的太阳能电池板必需的银粉几乎全部来自日本、美国和韩国。澳大利亚、加拿大和英国占中国用于电池和其他电气元件的镍粉和镍片进口量的约86%。中国从美国进口了近三分之二用于生产中国传统酒精“白酒”的高粱。</p><p>该分析定于周三在《国际安全》学术期刊上发表，使用了联合国商品贸易统计数据库（该数据库跟踪官方全球贸易统计数据）的数据。中国的高度依赖风险是通过将美国和十几个盟友的一系列贸易活动捆绑在一起计算得出的。</p><p>美国国家安全委员会前主任查表示，这些数据显示，如果美国和志同道合的伙伴共同采取行动，劝阻甚至惩罚中国的经济胁迫，那么它们的潜力有多大。</p><p> “我们所有的答案都是关于防守，而我们的答案都不是关于进攻，”查说。 “如果你愿意的话，两个人可以玩这个游戏。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="394" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832479?width=700&amp;height=394" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">中国通过限制包括挪威三文鱼在内的产品进口来对其他国家进行报复。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：陈亚勤/祖玛出版社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>CSIS 亚洲高级副总裁兼韩国主席 Cha 表示，他已与对研究结果表示感兴趣的政府官员分享了他的想法。他承认，困难的部分将是执行，获得公司和立法者的承诺，并阻止中国针对最薄弱环节的尝试。</p><p> “这就是为什么中国总觉得它可以孤立或欺凌任何国家，”他说。 “他们可以假设不会有任何集体反应。”</p><p>战略与国际研究中心之前的一些研究表明，中国的贸易限制和其他惩罚措施<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-pressure-tactics-against-other-countries-largely-ineffective-study-finds-3f49561f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">对于北京来说并没有取得成功</a>，因为一些目标国家最终与美国走得更近。</p><p>分析显示，日本对中国的高度依赖项目数量最多，为 124 个，其次是美国（87 个）、德国（64 个）、韩国（28 个）和法国（27 个）。美国是进口总额最大的国家，为 115 亿美元，而澳大利亚排名第二，为 106 亿美元。</p><p>根据国家安全威慑概念的原则，查认为应该建立一个经济联盟，其运作方式<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/what-is-nato-russia-ukraine-which-countries-members-no-fly-article-5-11646236897" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">类似于北约第五条的规定</a>，对任何成员国的攻击就是对所有成员国的攻击。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=607DAEAC-FDF3-4309-B753-4A08C846B405&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-s-allies-could-counter-chinas-economic-coercionif-they-unite-c45d2f8d&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">从喷气式飞机到电动汽车再到超级计算机，《华尔街日报》与不同的行业和技术专家讨论了两国在设计、工程和战略方面的匹配情况。照片插图：迈克尔·塔布和盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>查建议，这样的组织最初可能包括七国集团和澳大利亚，将制定税收优惠政策、评估处罚并建立预警系统以保持团结。当地立法将确保公司遵守对中国进口的限制。较大的国家可以设立一个基金，帮助稳定脆弱国家，如果北京在该组织成立时瞄准这些国家的话。</p><p>打击中国的经济胁迫已成为华盛顿及其西方和亚洲盟友日益关注的焦点。</p><p> 5月，拜登总统和七国集团其他领导人<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-fellow-g-7-leaders-take-on-china-at-hiroshima-summit-573108e0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">发表了一份异常尖锐的公报</a>，承诺“反击中国的恶行”并“增强抵御经济胁迫的能力”。七国集团没有点名中国，而是发起了一项倡议，通过共享信息、磋商和协调行动来应对经济胁迫案件。</p><p>美国及其密切合作伙伴成立了专注于电信、半导体和矿产等行业的新组织，以对抗中国的经济侵略。这些努力主要集中在减少供应链脆弱性。</p><p>中国对美国及其盟国提供的高度依赖产品的敞口约为470亿美元，仅占该国每年2.7万亿美元进口额的一小部分。但查说，北京关键行业面临的供应链风险值得警惕，因为连锁反应可能会导致更大的破坏。</p><p>关键是建立一个多边体系，让中国面临经济胁迫的后果——这在过去没有发生过。</p><p> “人们普遍意识到这个问题，并且愿意承认这是一个问题，”查说，“但我不认为这些国家感到受到保护。”</p><p>写信给 Timothy W. Martin，邮箱为<a href="mailto:Timothy.Martin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Timothy.Martin@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:58:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-allies-could-counter-chinas-economic-coercionif-they-unite-c45d2f8d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-allies-could-counter-chinas-economic-coercionif-they-unite-c45d2f8d<author><![CDATA[Timothy W. Martin]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. to Ban Some Investments in China]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>拜登的计划命令还将要求美国私募股权和风险投资公司披露某些投资<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001120961"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832248?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">拜登政府去年限制向中国出口先进半导体和芯片制造设备。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔纳森·恩斯特/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001120961"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/andrew-duehren" itemprop="url" rel="author">安德鲁·杜伦</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 9 日中午 12:35（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>根据拜登政府周三发布的一项行政命令，美国将从明年开始禁止对一些中国科技公司进行私募股权和风险投资，这将加大<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-looks-to-restrict-chinas-access-to-cloud-computing-to-protect-advanced-technology-f771613?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">华盛顿阻止北京为其军事开发尖端技术的力度</a>。</p><p>该行政命令将涵盖<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bidens-order-wont-destroy-chinese-venture-capital-6e23a26a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对中国三个技术领域的</a>直接投资：半导体、量子计算和人工智能。了解该命令的人士称，它将禁止对先进半导体和一些量子计算技术的投资。它还要求在中国做生意的美国人向美国政府通报更广泛的这三个高科技领域的投资情况。</p><p>知情人士表示，违反这些规定的投资者可能会面临罚款，并被迫剥离所持股份。知情人士表示，预计它们将适用于未来的交易，但不会涵盖中国股票和债券的投资组合。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>将与商务部一起管理这些规则的财政部发言人拒绝发表评论。拜登政府官员周三上午向立法者及其工作人员简要介绍了该行政命令。</p><p>这项行政命令是两党日益担心的产物，担心美国的技术和专门知识可能会无意中帮助北京开发可在军事冲突中用来对抗美国的武器。拜登政府去年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-u-s-uses-supply-chain-sway-to-throttle-chinas-chip-development-11666526403?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">限制向中国出口先进半导体</a>和芯片制造设备，美国也加强了对中国对美国科技公司投资的审查。</p><p>甚至在新的资本管制措施发布之前，它就已经开始重塑美国投资者的行为。经过华盛顿的持续审查，风险投资基金红杉资本<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sequoia-made-a-fortune-investing-in-the-u-s-and-china-then-it-had-to-pick-one-f13e7b91?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">今年早些时候剥离了其中国业务</a>。据知情人士透露，其他公司在等待新规定期间已经放缓或暂停了在中国的交易。</p><p>新的投资限制可能会导致两个超级大国之间试图解冻的外交关系重新冻结。尽管拜登政府官员将这些举措视为保护美国国家安全的有针对性的举措，但北京官员表示，这些举措的目的是限制中国的经济增长和发展。中国领导人习近平去年向拜登总统抱怨半导体出口管制。今年早些时候， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-bans-micron-as-supplier-to-big-chinese-firms-citing-national-security-5f326b90?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国禁止国内大公司</a>从美国最大的存储芯片制造商<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MU" class="">美光科技</a>购买技术<span class="company-name-type">，</span>此举被广泛解读为对美国出口限制的报复。</p><p>从技术上讲，这些规则预计也适用于对俄罗斯等其他对手的投资，但实际上它们预计只会影响美国对中国的投资。在明年执行新规则之前，预计拜登政府将接受有关实施规则的反馈。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=36C897CD-0391-4CD6-A2F4-AAB54C8FB90E&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-s-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">美国在20世纪50年代发明了太阳能电池板。但在全球市场上主导该技术的却是中国。 《华尔街日报》审视了该行业的权力动态，以及美国是否能够重新夺回其先锋地位。图片插图：Amogh Alva Vaz<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>近年来，随着地缘政治竞争加剧，美国对华投资曾帮助推动中国经济发展，但投资有所放缓。据荣鼎集团称，去年美国对华直接投资跌至 20 年来最低点 82 亿美元，该公司还表示，去年美国风险资本投资跌至 10 年来最低点 13 亿美元。</p><p>目前尚不清楚其中有多少资金流向了目标行业。乔治城大学研究人员的一份报告发现，2015年至2021年间，美国投资者参与了中国人工智能公司的401笔交易，同期纯美国投资者的投资额达74.5亿美元。</p><p>除了美国公司向中国公司提供的资金外，拜登政府官员还担心美国投资者经常向他们投资和帮助建立的公司提供的知识和指导。拜登政府官员认为，中国投资者可以取代硅谷可能提供的资金，但不一定能取代他们的技术头脑。</p><p>据知情人士透露，在起草行政命令时，拜登政府官员在如何区分主要构成国家安全风险的人工智能形式和广泛用于日常商业目的的其他形式人工智能方面遇到了困难。人工智能投资将受到披露要求的约束。</p><p>华盛顿的行业组织试图缩小拜登政府花了一年多时间制定的规则。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>美国对中国企业投资的最佳限制是什么？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>其他限制美国对华投资的提议范围更广。去年，一个由两党议员组成的小组呼吁成立一个跨部门小组，负责筛选更广泛技术领域的投资。今年，两位立法者在参议院通过的年度国防政策法案修正案中恢复了该计划的要素。他们的立法将要求披露投资，而不是禁止，并且可能不会成为法律。</p><p>威斯康星州共和党众议员迈克·加拉格尔 (Mike Gallagher) 和众议院中国事务委员会呼吁对流入中国的美国证券投资进行同样的限制。在最近的一封信中，该委员会批评<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/BLK" class="company-name">贝莱德</a>和顶级股市指数编制机构摩根士丹利资本国际(MSCI)为对中国公司的投资提供便利，美国政府指责这些公司支持中国军事并侵犯人权。</p><p>据知情人士透露，在拜登政府内部，财政部和商务部的官员已成功寻求限制行政命令的范围。财政部官员历来的任务是倡导美国对中国进行更多投资而不是限制投资，他们担心制定一套可能难以执行的规则。他们还希望保留美国的大量投资，并推动将规则针对对国家安全特别敏感的技术。</p><p>美国还一直在敦促其欧洲和亚洲盟友采取类似措施限制对中国的投资，希望阻止企业简单地通过伦敦或东京等地转移资金。经过美国的游说，七国集团在春季一致认为，资本管制“对于补充现有的针对出口和入境投资的定向控制工具可能很重要”。欧盟委员会建议这个由 27 个成员国组成的欧盟对海外投资采取限制措施。</p><p>写信给安德鲁·杜伦 (Andrew Duehren)，邮箱为<a href="mailto:andrew.duehren@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">andrew.duehren@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:35:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6<author><![CDATA[Andrew Duehren]]></author><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>超级计算机</category><category>信托/基金/金融工具</category><category>私人产权</category><category>另类投资</category><category>计算</category><category>电脑硬件</category><category>金融服务</category><category>金融科技</category><category>投资/证券</category><category>技术</category><category>风险投资</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>所有权变更</category><category>收购/合并/持股</category><category>研究和发展</category><category>收购/合并</category><category>企业行动</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>所有权变更</category><category>收购</category><category>合并</category><category>持股</category><category>研究</category><category>发展</category><category>企业行动</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>超级计算机</category><category>信托</category><category>资金</category><category>金融工具</category><category>私人产权</category><category>另类投资</category><category>计算</category><category>电脑硬件</category><category>金融服务</category><category>金融科技</category><category>投资</category><category>证券</category><category>技术</category><category>风险投资</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Saudis Agree With U.S. on Path to Normalize Kingdom’s Ties With Israel]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>官员们正在谈判他们希望在 9 到 12 个月内巩固的协议细节，但障碍仍然存在<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121274"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="564" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832348?width=860&amp;height=564" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">沙特王储穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼上个月在吉达与拜登政府会面，以加快谈判进程。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121274"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dion-nissenbaum" itemprop="url" rel="author">迪昂·尼森鲍姆</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 9 日中午 12:30（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-saudi-arabia-agree-to-broad-terms-for-israel-normalization-ac6d549c"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>华盛顿——据美国官员称，美国和沙特阿拉伯已就一项协议的大致轮廓达成一致<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/saudi-arabia-moves-toward-eventual-ties-with-israel-11654517783?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，沙特阿拉伯将承认以色列，</a>以换取对巴勒斯坦人的让步、美国的安全保证和民用核帮助。</p><p>美国官员表示谨慎乐观，认为在未来 9 到 12 个月内，他们可以敲定一代人以来最重要的中东和平协议的更详细细节。但他们警告说，他们的胜算很小。</p><p>两周前，沙特王储穆罕默德·本·萨勒曼在吉达与拜登总统的国家安全顾问杰克·沙利文会面，以加速谈判，随后加大了努力力度。谈判代表现在已开始讨论具体细节，包括<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/saudi-arabia-seeks-u-s-security-pledges-nuclear-help-for-peace-with-israel-cd47baaf?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">满足沙特要求</a>美国帮助他们开发民用核计划并提供铁定安全保证的要求。</p><p>沙特还寻求以色列做出重大让步，以帮助促进巴勒斯坦国的建立。作为回报，美国正在敦促沙特阿拉伯限制<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/saudi-arabia-strengthens-relations-with-china-amid-strained-u-s-ties-c5819114?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">其与中国不断发展的关系</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="471" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832349?width=700&amp;height=471" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">以色列国家安全顾问查奇·哈内格比表示，谈判代表尚未向以色列领导人提出具体想法。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：弗朗索瓦·勒努瓦/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>一位美国高级官员表示：“有一项工作计划来探索这将是什么的要素，并测试可能性的界限。”</p><p>美国官员称，这些努力是华盛顿、利雅得和耶路撒冷认识到现在是试图达成协议的时候的结果。拜登试图筛选美国在中东的军事存在，并建立一个能够在美国有限支持下应对伊朗威胁的地区安全联盟。</p><p>尽管美国官员表示，拜登尚未决定他愿意付出什么代价，但总统对这笔交易的关注反映了他的观点，即美国必须继续在中东发挥核心作用<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-held-secret-meeting-with-israeli-arab-military-chiefs-to-counter-iran-air-threat-11656235802?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，以遏制伊朗</a>、 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-allies-stick-together-to-confront-russia-and-chinafor-now-76156bf7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">孤立俄罗斯</a>。乌克兰战争并挫败中国取代华盛顿在该地区利益的努力。</p><p> 《华尔街日报》的报道周三在网上发表后，国家安全委员会发言人约翰·柯比表示，谈判人员还有很长的路要走。 “我们和我们的朋友在该地区没有商定的一系列谈判，也没有商定的框架来规范关系正常化或任何其他安全考虑，”他说。</p><p>美国官员表示，为了换取美国对沙特阿拉伯的让步，拜登政府正在寻求沙特阿拉伯的保证，即它将在经济和军事上与中国保持距离。</p><p>官员们表示，美国可以寻求沙特阿拉伯的保证，不会允许中国在该国建立军事基地——这个问题已成为拜登政府和阿联酋之间的痛点。他们表示，谈判代表还可能寻求限制沙特阿拉伯使用中国华为开发的技术，并保证利雅得将使用美元而不是人民币来定价石油销售。预计美国还将寻找方法来结束因沙特阿拉伯多次减产而引发的油价争端。</p><p>穆罕默德对于他对不同受众的承诺给出了相互矛盾的信息。处理这一问题的美国官员表示，穆罕默德非常认真地试图促成一项协议。但据沙特官员称，王储告诉助手，他还没有准备好与以色列建立类似于与阿拉伯联合酋长国的全面外交关系，后者于 2020 年签署了一项协议。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832360?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">以色列士兵最近在以色列占领的西岸拉马拉附近站岗，巴勒斯坦人希望该地区成为独立国家的一部分。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Gil Cohen Magen/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>他们说，王储告诉他的顾问，他并不着急，尤其是以色列目前的强硬联合政府反对建立独立的巴勒斯坦国。</p><p>华盛顿中东研究所政策副所长布莱恩·卡图利斯将这一努力比作登山者试图连续攀登珠穆朗玛峰。</p><p> “这是一个非常危险的景观，”他说。 “他们需要做四五件事，以确保他们不会凭空离开山。对我来说，短期内这似乎不太可能，但谁知道呢？”</p><p>谈判人员面临的障碍之一是以色列必须向巴勒斯坦人做出哪些让步，以换取与沙特阿拉伯建立开放的外交关系。美国和沙特官员表示，以色列必须提出重大提议，推动建立独立巴勒斯坦国的努力。</p><p>以色列领导人在会谈中淡化巴勒斯坦问题的重要性。以色列总理</p>本杰明·内塔尼亚胡本周早些时候表示，谈判中出现的这个问题“比你想象的要少得多”。<p></p><p> “这有点像一个复选框，”他告诉彭博新闻社。 “你必须检查一下，才能证明你正在做这件事。”</p><p>据了解讨论情况的人士透露，这个问题仍然是谈判中最不成熟的问题之一。</p><p>以色列国家安全顾问查奇·哈内格比表示，谈判代表尚未向以色列领导人提出具体想法。 “目前，我们甚至不知道从哪里开始，”他说。 “他们仍在处理彼此之间的基本问题。因此，显然他们现在讨论这个问题还为时过早。”</p><p>沙特官员对不妥协且分裂且民众支持有限的巴勒斯坦领导人的耐心越来越少。但作为伊斯兰教最重要的两个圣地的所在地，沙特阿拉伯正在寻求以色列做出有意义的让步，以抵御伊朗和土耳其竞争对手的批评，后者指责沙特王国粉碎了巴勒斯坦独立国家的梦想。巴勒斯坦问题对于沙特阿拉伯和世界各地的活动人士来说仍然很重要。</p><p>内塔尼亚胡明确表示，他只愿意向巴勒斯坦人做出适度让步，即使这些让步也可能面临其强硬联盟伙伴的反对，这些伙伴希望吞并以色列占领的约旦河西岸巴勒斯坦土地。</p><p>以色列官员还对沙特阿拉伯寻求发展核能计划表示担忧，他们认为这是加速地区核军备竞赛的危险行为。尽管以色列不会公开承认，但它是该地区唯一拥有核武器的国家，它不希望看到其他国家加入这个小俱乐部。</p><p>以色列官员担心，美国对沙特阿拉伯民用核计划的支持可能为利雅得发展核武器铺平道路，穆罕默德表示，如果伊朗首先这样做，他就会这样做。</p><p>以色列总理哈内比表示，他“完全相信”在这个问题上“无论美国做出什么决定”都将解决以色列的担忧。</p><p>预计协议细节也将在国会受到审查，许多立法者不愿向穆罕默德让步。美国情报官员表示，穆罕默德在 2018 年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bolton-calls-khashoggi-death-a-heinous-crime-1543942052?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">为沙特派遣一支突击队前往伊斯坦布尔</a>刺杀记者贾迈勒·卡舒吉开了绿灯。</p><p>美国立法者已经对美国向沙特阿拉伯提供受条约约束的保证的前景表示担忧，即如果沙特受到攻击，美国将保卫该国——这一保证需要参议院批准。即使是不需要国会明确支持的较小安全保证也可能会在华盛顿面临阻力。</p><p> Some lawmakers are opposed to talk of expanding arms sales to Saudi Arabia, which Biden put limits on when he took office in 2021 to protest the kingdom&#39;s use of American weapons in Yemen.</p><p> If the US can negotiate a package that is acceptable to Saudi, Israeli, Palestinian, and Congressional leaders, the Biden administration is then hoping that global pressure to support a history-shifting deal would prompt opposition parties in Israel to join forces with Netanyahu and endorse the agreement, something they so far have refused to consider.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> — <em>Summer Said in Dubai and Dov Lieber in Tel Aviv</em> contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Dion Nissenbaum at <a href="mailto:dion.nissenbaum@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dion.nissenbaum@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-saudi-arabia-agree-to-broad-terms-for-israel-normalization-ac6d549c</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-saudi-arabia-agree-to-broad-terms-for-israel-normalization-ac6d549c<author><![CDATA[Dion Nissenbaum]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>Nuclear Weapons Programs</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>Weapons Programs</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>nuclear weapons programs</category><category>政治</category><category>weapons programs </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Sputtering Trade Fuels Fears for a Connected World]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Cyclical factors are weighing on commerce, but the specter of global economic divisions lurks in the background <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121519"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="644" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832429?width=860&amp;height=644" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Higher interest rates in the US, Europe and other economies battling with inflation have led to a broad global slowdown.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Cfoto/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121519"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/marcus-walker" itemprop="url" rel="author">Marcus Walker</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/yuka-hayashi" itemprop="url" rel="author">Yuka Hayashi</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 9, 2023 11:17 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sputtering-trade-fuels-fears-for-a-connected-world-81c99922"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> The downturn in world trade, exemplified by <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-exports-fall-at-steepest-pace-since-february-2020-e930246b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">slumping Chinese exports</a> and a decline in US imports, mainly reflects a phase of weak global economic growth.</p><p> It also raises questions about whether deeper changes are under way, with decades of deepening global economic integration giving way to a new era in which the West and China do more business with their political friends and less with each other.</p><p> Geopolitical tensions, heightened by <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/returning-ukrainian-refugees-say-theres-no-place-like-home-56cd2969?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Russia&#39;s invasion of Ukraine</a> , are leading to more curbs in the US and Europe on <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">doing business with China</a> . The sheer scale and complexity of global trade and investment links, however, mean any process of disentangling the world economy into blocks of like-minded countries is likely to be gradual and incomplete.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-global-economy-looks-like-its-out-of-sync-a645f025?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Global trade is currently weak</a> mostly because demand for goods is weak, economists say. Higher interest rates in the US, Europe and other economies battling with inflation have led to a broad global slowdown.</p><p> In addition, consumers who spent heavily on goods during and after the Covid-19 pandemic are now spending more of their disposable income on services, which—with exceptions such as tourism—are more likely to be locally produced. Manufacturing-heavy economies in Asia are <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-drop-in-exports-signals-deepening-slowdown-in-global-trade-df03bb29?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">feeling the fallout</a> .</p><p> Trade in services is livelier than shipments of goods, thanks not least to the rebound in international travel and tourism, which is expected to recover this year to nearly its prepandemic level.</p><p> Inflation itself is also weighing on trade. <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/inflation-is-cooling-food-inflation-could-get-worse-bb373e06?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Food and energy prices remain higher</a> than before Russia launched its full-scale invasion of Ukraine in early 2022, cutting into people&#39;s disposable income around the world, even though commodity prices such as grain and natural gas have fallen from their peaks last year.</p><p> “The main story is probably related to the global slowdown in manufacturing, after the big surge in manufacturing that followed the pandemic,” said Lorenzo Codogno, chief economist at LC Macro Advisors and a visiting professor at the London School of Economics. “Fragmentation, deglobalization, de-risking will play a bigger role in the coming years and could be very significant. But I&#39;m skeptical that it can happen overnight,” Codogno said.</p><p> Resilient <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-economy-retail-sales-june-2023-ac582986?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">US consumer demand</a> , helped by strong wage growth, has been a bright spot for the world economy. But the Federal Reserve&#39;s interest-rate increases are weighing on business investment, including spending on capital goods.</p><p> Trade data is beginning to reflect that. In the first half of this year, overall US imports declined 4% from a year earlier, while exports grew 2.6%, the Commerce Department said Tuesday. Imports fell 1% in June from May to $313 billion, the lowest level since December 2021.</p><p> “Though the holiday season may bring some improvement to trade flows, we expect strong headwinds in the form of elevated interest rates, softening consumer demand, and a mild recession to prevent a sustained recovery until 2024,” Matthew Martin, US economist for Oxford Economics said in a research note on Tuesday.</p><p> The International Monetary Fund expects growth in global trade to slow to 2% this year from 5.2% last year. The World Bank and the World Trade Organization both forecast trade will grow <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-war-and-inflation-to-limit-global-trade-growth-in-2023-wto-says-c3d7adee?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">by just 1.7% this year</a> .</p><p> Even a partial recovery in 2024 is predicted to fall well short of trade&#39;s average yearly growth of 4.9% during the two decades before the pandemic.</p><p> Economists at the IMF and other multilateral organizations mainly blame sluggish overall growth, especially in advanced economies. But they have also expressed concern about the long-term effect of geopolitical rivalries on global trade, with possible emergence of a trading bloc surrounding China and Russia an additional around the US and its allies.</p><p> “We see the increase in trade restrictions that have been imposed by countries on one another,” IMF chief economist Pierre-Olivier Gourinchas said in late July, pointing to a spread of tariffs and restrictive regulations. “There is an impact in terms of direct investment also and that is quite important.”</p><p> The US is expected to announce fresh curbs on investment in some Chinese technology companies, a further move to restrict Chinese access to American know-how following last year&#39;s restrictions on the export of advanced semiconductors and chip-manufacturing equipment.</p><p> The Biden administration has also <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-might-soon-ease-chinese-tariffs-in-a-decision-fraught-with-policy-tensions-11656927001?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">kept in place most of the tariffs</a> on goods from China and other countries implemented by the Trump administration.</p><p> Many European countries are clamping down on Chinese investments in the region, and the continent&#39;s leaders are looking for ways to reduce their dependence on China for critical raw materials and other inputs. But companies from Germany and other countries that have built up a heavy reliance on the Chinese market are resisting political calls to scale back.</p><p> The West&#39;s efforts to isolate Russia show <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-west-attacked-russias-economy-the-result-is-another-stalemate-99ec913b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">how difficult it can be</a> to untangle globalization. Despite sanctions on Moscow and calls for businesses to pull out, many European and US companies continue to operate in Russia. Spikes in German exports to countries neighboring Russia, such as Georgia and Kazakhstan, are fueling suspicions that Russia is still importing many Western products via roundabout routes.</p><p> On the other hand, European countries have replaced the bulk of Russian oil and natural gas with other sources, while Russia is redirecting its energy exports to China and other customers, showing how war can lead to rapid shifts.</p><p> Other recent geographical shifts include the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-europe-trade-booms-as-old-allies-draw-closer-11668914679?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">US and Europe trading more</a> with each other, even as Western trade with China slows; Mexico supplanting China as the US&#39;s largest trade partner; and developing countries shifting their exports to China rather than the West.</p><p> The pace and patterns of globalization have shifted before. The world economy rapidly became more interconnected after the end of the Cold War and the collapse of Communism, and particularly after China joined the WTO in 2001. For years, cross-border trade and investment rose as a share of global economic activity.</p><p> But globalization began to stagnate after the 2008 global financial crisis. Trade no longer grew faster than the overall world economy, but it didn&#39;t sharply decline either.</p><p> Most economists agree that the rise of trade has been enormously beneficial overall, helping to lift hundreds of millions of people out of poverty and boosting overall output in both advanced and developing economies. But the gains haven&#39;t been spread evenly, with middle-to-lower-income workers in rich countries often feeling left behind, fueling a political backlash.</p><p> A return to higher tariffs and other forms of trade protection followed, notably under the Trump administration. Now, the war in Ukraine has brought back the specter of “great power” conflicts, including between China and the US, and with it a push for more economic barriers.</p><p> In the early 20th century, it was <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-military-china-taiwan-russia-great-power-conflict-481f7756?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">great power wars</a> that ended the first era of deeply interconnected global trade, with a revival coming only after the fall of the Berlin Wall.</p><p> Many economists worry that a reversal of this century&#39;s boom in trade would carry a heavy economic cost, bringing higher prices and lower efficiency if production moves to politically allied shores. “Economically, a real division of the world into two blocs would be a big loss,” said Codogno.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Jason Douglas contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Marcus Walker at <a href="mailto:Marcus.Walker@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Marcus.Walker@wsj.com</a> and Yuka Hayashi at <a href="mailto:Yuka.Hayashi@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Yuka.Hayashi@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:17:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/sputtering-trade-fuels-fears-for-a-connected-world-81c99922</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/sputtering-trade-fuels-fears-for-a-connected-world-81c99922<author><![CDATA[Marcus WalkerYuka Hayashi]]></author><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>Economic Growth/Recession</category><category> Trade/External Payments</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>International Sanctions</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>Trade Barriers/Restrictions</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>economic growth</category><category> recession</category><category>贸易</category><category>external payments</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>international sanctions</category><category>政治</category><category>trade barriers</category><category> restrictions </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta, Alphabet and Other Tech Firms Face New Data Rules in India]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Companies must get explicit permission from users for data handling, but the law carves out many exemptions for the government <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121405"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832408?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The bill allows the government to limit the transfer of data outside India.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Dhiraj Singh/Bloomberg News </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121405"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/newley-purnell" itemprop="url" rel="author">Newley Purnell</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/tripti-lahiri" itemprop="url" rel="author">Tripti Lahiri</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 9, 2023 10:13 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/meta-alphabet-and-other-tech-firms-face-new-data-rules-in-india-90a68e7f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> India&#39;s Parliament on Wednesday passed a data-protection bill years in the making that the government says is needed to regulate tech companies and protect citizens, but that rights groups say gives New Delhi too much power.</p><p> The bill, called <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/for-u-s-tech-indias-draft-privacy-bill-has-hidden-risks-11669989692?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the Digital Personal Data Protection Act</a> , says that companies must get consent from users before collecting their personal data and that they must use it for the stated purposes. It allows the government to limit the transfer of data outside India and penalizes companies for breaking the rules.</p><p> “Many platforms and many companies…have been collecting personal data of citizens, not just in India but all around the world,” said the junior technology minister, Rajeev Chandrasekhar, in a video posted on X, previously known as Twitter, last week, when the legislation was introduced in the lower house of India&#39;s Parliament. Technology companies “essentially creating business models by misusing and exploiting digital personal data of citizens is something that this bill intends to address.”</p><p> Rights groups, however, argue that the legislation gives the government excessive power. It doesn&#39;t create an independent regulator and allows the government to exempt itself from the bill&#39;s obligations, according to digital-rights group Access Now. One provision adds to the government&#39;s ability to block online information, <strong>&nbsp;</strong> while another partly dilutes a transparency law enabling citizens to get information from public authorities.</p><p> The Editors Guild, a press association, in a statement expressed concern over what it called a “widening of censorship powers” in the bill.</p><p> “This will increase censorship powers well beyond what is presently provided for…and may even be unconstitutional,” the group said.</p><p> While the bill represents a significant step in enhancing users&#39; privacy protections and will mandate companies to manage data more responsibly, it also allows authorities to collect data without individuals&#39; consent “under exceptional circumstances, potentially paving the way for an infrastructure of mass surveillance,” said Akshara Bassi, a senior research analyst at technology market research firm Counterpoint Research.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> The ministry for information technology didn&#39;t immediately respond to a request for comment.</p><p> A date for enactment hasn&#39;t been announced. An internet-policy expert noted that the bill leaves many specifics, including which territories might be blocked from data transfers, to be dealt with under rules that will be drafted by the government to implement the law.</p><p> “There is a lot of discretion and control that the executive is retaining for itself,” said Prateek Waghre, policy director at the Internet Freedom Foundation, an Indian digital-rights organization, adding that companies won&#39;t fully know how the law could impact them until those rules are out.</p><p> An earlier version of the bill released in 2018 prompted concern among tech companies that it would be onerous to implement. The US flagged that version of the bill in an annual report on trade barriers as an initiative that could “potentially threaten innovation and economic growth.”</p><p> The rules are <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/indias-face-off-with-big-tech-will-intensify-in-2023-11672809328" target="_blank" class="icon none">the latest challenge to American technology companies</a> that have hundreds of millions of users in the world&#39;s most populous democracy.</p><p> New Delhi has in recent years passed rules to counter the rise of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/facebook-whatsapp-and-twitter-face-new-rules-in-india-11614250424?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">problematic material online</a> , <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-tech-giants-bet-big-on-india-now-the-rules-are-changing-11575386675" target="_blank" class="icon none">tightened e-commerce regulations</a> , and cracked down on <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/global-vpn-providers-pull-india-servers-over-new-cybersecurity-rules-11662024603" target="_blank" class="icon none">virtual private networks</a> , which let internet users shield their identities online.</p><p> Indian government officials have in past years spoken about the need for data sovereignty in India and articulated a desire for homegrown tech startups to flourish as they have in China, where American players are locked out.</p><p> US tech companies such as <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/META" class="company-name">Meta</a> Platforms, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GOOG" class="">Alphabet</a> <span class="company-name-type">&#39;s</span> Google and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AMZN" class="company-name">Amazon.com</a></p> have hundreds of millions of users in India. They have also been <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/facebook-takes-5-7-billion-stake-in-indias-jio-11587521592?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">investing billions of dollars</a> in the South Asian nation, the world&#39;s last great untapped tech market, where hundreds of millions of people have been getting online for the first time thanks to inexpensive smartphones and cheap mobile data.<p></p><p> Amazon and Meta declined to comment. A representative for Google didn&#39;t immediately respond to a request for comment.</p><p> India&#39;s digital economy should grow from about $175 billion last year to about $1 trillion by 2030, according to a June report from Google, Singapore state-investment company Temasek Holdings and consulting firm Bain &amp; Company.</p><p> Write to Newley Purnell at <a href="mailto:newley.purnell@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">newley.purnell@wsj.com</a> and Tripti Lahiri at <a href="mailto:tripti.lahiri@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">tripti.lahiri@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 14:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/meta-alphabet-and-other-tech-firms-face-new-data-rules-in-india-90a68e7f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/meta-alphabet-and-other-tech-firms-face-new-data-rules-in-india-90a68e7f<author><![CDATA[Newley PurnellTripti Lahiri]]></author><category> Internet Search Engines</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>Media/Entertainment</category><category> Social Media Platforms/Tools</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Privacy Issues/Information Security</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E Industry News Filter</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>privacy issues</category><category>信息安全</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e industry news filter</category><category> internet search engines</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category><category>社交媒体平台</category><category>工具</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[New Tax Rules Can Save You Thousands on Home Renovations]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Coming rebates for energy-efficient upgrades can be combined with existing tax credits <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832084/?width=2000&amp;size=1.949" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> PHOTO ILLUSTRATION BY ELENA SCOTTI/THE WALL STREET JOURNAL, ISTOCK (2) <span>PHOTO ILLUSTRATION BY ELENA SCOTTI/THE WALL STREET JOURNAL, ISTOCK (2)</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119846"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001119846"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ashlea-ebeling" itemprop="url" rel="author">Ashlea Ebeling</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 9 日上午 9:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tax-rebates-energy-efficient-home-improvements-renovation-e6cdb19a"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> Many Americans will save thousands of dollars on home renovations when new rebates for a range of energy-efficient upgrades kick in later this year.</p><p> Buyers will receive the rebates as part of a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-biden-to-sign-bill-aimed-at-lowering-drug-costs-boosting-renewable-energy-11660642202?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">$9 billion federal program</a> passed by Congress in last summer&#39;s Inflation Reduction Act. Household savings can range from hundreds of dollars for single items such as an electric cooktop or dryer to $8,000 for a heat pump or cutting home energy use by 35% or more. Those planning such projects may want to hold off until the program begins.</p><p> The size of the rebates will vary based on your household income and where you live, since the program will be administered separately by each state.</p><p> States will announce the particulars in coming months, based on guidelines issued by the Energy Department in July. These rebates can also be stacked on top of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/electric-vehicle-tax-credits-energy-dbb32864?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">existing tax credits</a> and utility offers for heat pumps, solar and EVs, said Kara Saul-Rinaldi, a clean-energy policy strategist in Washington, DC The new rebate programs and enhanced tax credits are good through 2032. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          edgetoedge
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/18779d33-b7f3-4536-9414-0b3dd6012b83.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> These rebates are intended to boost conversion of more homes to energy-efficient technologies at a time when scorching temperatures and other extreme weather have raised the costs of cooling, heating and powering homes. The average <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/air-conditioning-electricity-bills-energy-f3dce1a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">US household energy costs</a> in June, July and August will rise nationwide by 11.7% to $578, compared with last year, according to the National Energy Assistance Directors Association. The rebates are also meant to offset the impact inflation has had on the cost of renovations, energy policy analysts said.</p><p> A low-income household, defined as below 80% of an area&#39;s median income, could claim up to $22,250 to fully cover energy efficiency upgrades, Saul-Rinaldi said.</p><p> A moderate-income household, earning between 80% and 150% of area median income, could potentially get $19,000 in incentives on a $32,000 project.</p><p> Above that, a higher-income household could get $7,200 on a home performance retrofit, a combination of $4,000 in rebates and $3,200 in tax credits. (In Los Angeles County, for example, 150% of median family income is $147,300.)</p><p> Here&#39;s how to strategize claiming the existing credits and the new rebates, depending what type of remodel you need and have the budget for. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=73DA72E0-DF39-4F23-973C-AEEBEF455473&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ftax-rebates-energy-efficient-home-improvements-renovation-e6cdb19a&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">美国西南部的一个巨大的热穹正在推动菲尼克斯和拉斯维加斯的气温创下三位数的新高。新的 Maxar 卫星照片显示了这些城市的发展如何导致了酷热。插图：卢卡·德帕东<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><h3>Start with a home-energy audit</h3><p> A good first step homeowners can take toward increasing energy-efficiency and electrification is a home-energy audit, said Saul-Rinaldi. Getting one will be a requirement for the new rebate program for cutting overall energy use.</p><p> The Internal Revenue Service issued guidance last week specifying that the audit must identify the most significant and cost-effective energy-efficiency improvements, including an estimate of the energy and cost savings to each improvement. Taxpayers can get a $150 tax credit for a $500 audit. By doing an audit this year, you can have a plan in place for when the state rebates roll out.</p><h3> Spread out home improvements to boost savings</h3><p> Cynthia Adams bought a 1959 ranch-style house in Durango, Colo., last year and is now plotting out how to best use federal and state incentives to make it fully electric. The first thing she did was upgrade the refrigerator, washer/dryer and front door with Energy Star-rated replacements, snagging a $40 utility rebate for the new fridge and a $100 tax credit for the new door. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832031?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Cynthia Adams hopes to make her 1959 ranch-style house in Durango, Colo., fully electric.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Cynthia Adams</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Next up: insulation and air sealing for the attic and crawl space and a new heat-pump heating and cooling system. Then solar.</p><p> She&#39;ll likely qualify for a $2,000 rebate under the new home-retrofit program, and would stack the federal tax credit of up to $2,000 for a heat pump. She&#39;s also eyeing a $1,000 heat-pump rebate offered by her local electric co-op. The tax credit for solar is worth 30% of the project costs.</p><p> “I&#39;ll have to stage things. Budget and time are issues for me, like most people,” she said.</p><h3> Use apps to help crunch the numbers</h3><p> The mix of green incentives is becoming so complicated that new free apps are rushing in to help homeowners sort it all out.</p><p> Pearl Certification&#39;s Green Door app helps guide homeowners through high-performance renovations, from picking a contractor and searching for rebates by your home&#39;s address to documenting the improvements.</p><p> Rewiring America has an Inflation Reduction Act calculator that lets you plug in your family income and ZIP Code. It also produces a list of available upfront rebates and tax credits.</p><h3> Claiming the energy-efficient home-improvement tax credit</h3><p> Under revamped tax credits, homeowners can get up to $1,200 for insulation and other items, and up to $2,000 for a heat pump, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/electric-vehicle-tax-credits-energy-dbb32864?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">calculated at 30% of the costs</a> . A tax credit lowers your tax bill dollar for dollar.</p><p> It is an annual credit, meaning you could take it one year for putting in new windows, and another year for adding insulation. You can claim improvements made in 2023 on IRS Form 5695 when you file taxes next year. You can&#39;t get back more than you owe in taxes, and you can&#39;t carry forward any excess to future tax years. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="793" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832021?width=639&amp;height=793" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Craig Foley is making his circa 1895 Victorian in Melrose, Mass., more energy efficient in part to make it more marketable.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Craig Foley</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3> Adding value to your house for resale</h3><p> One of the reasons Craig Foley, a Realtor in Melrose, Mass., embarked on an electrification remodel to his circa 1895 Victorian house was to make it more marketable. He started his house redo in 2021 with the building envelope, taking the home down to the studs and adding new insulation to the 4-inch walls. He got $10,700 in state rebates last year for installing two heat pumps, one for heating and cooling and another to heat hot water.</p><p> Up next is installing an EV charger for his plug-in hybrid Subaru Crosstrek and solar panels to get the house running close to net zero.</p><p> “I want it to compete in a changing market when we decide to sell,” he said.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          inline
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>How do tax credits and rebates factor into your home renovation plans?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> Write to Ashlea Ebeling at <a href="mailto:ashlea.ebeling@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ashlea.ebeling@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 13:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/tax-rebates-energy-efficient-home-improvements-renovation-e6cdb19a</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/tax-rebates-energy-efficient-home-improvements-renovation-e6cdb19a<author><![CDATA[Ashlea Ebeling]]></author><category> WSJ生活工作</category><category>gfx-contrib</category><category> Building Construction</category><category> Residential Building Construction</category><category> Construction</category><category> Real Estate/Construction</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算/税收</category><category>Direct Taxation</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>Income Tax</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Energy Efficiency</category><category> Energy Efficient Home Improvements</category><category>自然环境</category><category>Home Improvements</category><category> Living/Lifestyle</category><category> Real Estate/Property</category><category> Sustainable Development/Sustainability</category><category> SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>家居与园艺</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算</category><category>税收</category><category>direct taxation</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>所得税</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>能源效率</category><category>energy efficient home improvements</category><category>自然环境</category><category>home improvements</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>房地产</category><category>财产</category><category>可持续发展</category><category>可持续性</category><category>家居与花园</category><category>building construction</category><category> residential building construction</category><category>建造</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[China Slips Into Deflation in Warning Sign for Global Economy]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>取消 Covid-19 大流行限制后，消费者价格出现了不寻常的下跌，而不是飙升<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121031"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832242?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">中国两年来首次陷入通货紧缩。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：马克·R·克里斯蒂诺/Shutterstock </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121031"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/stella-yifan-xie" itemprop="url" rel="author">谢一凡</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 9 日上午 5:21 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-slips-into-deflation-in-warning-sign-for-world-economy-bbefb179"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>香港——世界第二大经济体的消费需求不温不火，经济担忧加剧，使中国两年来首次陷入通货紧缩，这给北京带来了更大的压力，要求其采取更积极的行动，以避免经济不景气加剧。</p><p>去年年底取消Covid-19大流行限制后，中国并没有经历价格飙升，而是一系列商品的价格出现了不寻常的下跌，从钢铁和煤炭等大宗商品到日常必需品和消费品，例如蔬菜和家用电器。</p><p>中国的经济困境与美国和其他发达西方经济体<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/while-everyone-else-fights-inflation-chinas-deflation-fears-deepen-4045cabf?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">形成鲜明对比</a>，美国和其他发达西方经济体在解除新冠限制后通胀飙升，导致包括美联储在内的各国央行采取激进的加息方式，旨在在不影响经济的情况下给经济降温。引发经济衰退。</p><p>虽然随着中国出口产品变得更便宜，中国价格下跌可能有助于缓解其他地方的通胀压力，但它们可能成为全球经济的另一个担忧的根源。例如，大量低价中国商品可能会挤压其他国家生产商的利润并损害就业机会。</p><p> 7月份中国居民消费价格同比下降0.3%。美国最新数据显示， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/consumer-price-index-report-june-inflation-ede7f4b1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">6 月份消费者价格同比上涨 3%</a> ，为两年多以来最慢涨幅，而欧盟年度通胀率为 6.4%，低于 5 月份的 7.1%。</p><p>对于中国来说，通胀的缺失反映出经济的不平衡，其特点是供给充足，而内需却处于休眠状态，经济学家表示，北京必须采取更多措施来唤醒内需。</p><p>但这种反弹很快就<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-economy-stutters-forward-as-growth-concerns-linger-1be8acb2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">消失了</a>。与此同时，由于<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/xi-china-economy-capital-investment-3439d31a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">与西方经济体的地缘政治紧张局势加剧</a>以及针对中国一些最赚钱行业的监管打压，私营企业的投资降至疫情前的水平以下。</p><p>与此同时，青年失业率<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-youth-unemployment-xi-jobs-522028c5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">飙升至一系列历史新高</a>，6 月份达到 21.3%。随着西方世界的需求枯竭，作为新冠疫情期间的经济支柱的中国出口现在正<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-exports-fall-at-steepest-pace-since-february-2020-e930246b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">以多年来最快的速度下降</a>。</p><p>目前，中国决策者对物价下跌持乐观态度，否认通货紧缩将持续的说法。中国央行今年已多次降息，但财政和货币政策制定者都没有推出任何更大规模的刺激措施，部分原因是债务水平上升等限制。</p><p> “现实看起来越来越严峻，”康奈尔大学贸易政策和经济学教授、国际货币基金组织中国部前负责人埃斯瓦尔·普拉萨德(Eswar Prasad)表示。 “政府淡化通货紧缩和增长停滞风险的做法可能会适得其反，使经济摆脱螺旋式下降的难度加大。” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832305?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>中国国家统计局公布的数据显示，自去年10月以来，出厂价格同比下降，7月份出厂价格同比下降4.4%，降幅较6月份的5.4%收窄。周三。</p><p>但标志着更大转变的是消费者价格通胀，尽管生产者价格转为负值，但消费者价格通胀仍保持正值。继 6 月持平后，上个月下降 0.3%，这是自 2021 年 2 月以来的首次下降，与大流行初期（当时供应链和食品价格混乱）相比，这一读数与去年同期相比有所偏差。</p><p>除了2020年11月疫情对经济造成冲击之外，自2009年全球金融危机最严重时期以来，消费者价格和生产者价格从未同时处于通缩区域。</p><p>中国国家统计局发言人周三表示，7月份消费者价格通缩主要是由于食品价格较上年同期下降，去年食品价格因<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-extends-power-curbs-amid-heat-wave-drought-11661171568?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">极端天气条件</a>而推高。中国人的主食猪肉价格 7 月份同比下跌 26%。上个月蔬菜价格也有所下降。</p><p>剔除波动较大的食品和能源价格，所谓的核心通胀率从 6 月份的 0.4% 升至 7 月份的 0.8%，为 1 月份以来的最高水平。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=E87CB6AE-077A-4221-86C2-EE6981C09C4C&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fchina-slips-into-deflation-in-warning-sign-for-world-economy-bbefb179&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">美国生产的玉米比任何其他作物都多，去年美国农场向中国出售了价值 53 亿美元的玉米。但中国多年来一直在吸引其他生产商，并且正在探索实现长期自给自足的方法。插图：赵安妮<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>即便如此，经济学家表示，今年消费者通胀也不太可能大幅上升。原因是消费者信心，或者更确切地说是缺乏信心，因为家庭继续感受到三年来新冠疫情的不确定性、监管的不确定性以及对房地产市场健康状况的持续担忧所带来的挥之不去的影响。房地产行业是中国几十年来经济增长的主要推动力之一，但目前却陷入了深深的恐慌，本周<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/country-garden-chinas-largest-surviving-developer-sinks-into-debt-crisis-2a525173?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">围绕中国最大房地产开发商之一的默认担忧</a>引发了新的担忧。</p><p>与许多西方国家不同的是，政府在疫情期间向消费者发放现金，推动了家具和个人电子产品等实物商品的消费热潮，但北京迄今为止尚未向其家庭提供此类直接支持。</p><p>魏耀表示，除此之外， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-property-market-enters-troubling-new-phase-1fe3143d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">房地产市场的重新低迷</a>抑制了中国消费者的消费欲望，因为许多家庭将公寓作为主要的财富储存手段，对房价波动高度敏感。法国兴业银行中国经济学家。</p><p> “问题是目前没有明显的电力恢复驱动因素，”她说。</p><p>王雷说，除了装修两年前购买的一套公寓外，他和妻子的总体支出与去年相比有所下降。看到同事和朋友被解雇，他感到害怕，开始控制任何不必要的开支。</p><p> “现在最好多存一点，谨慎一点，”40 岁的王说，他在北京一家视频游戏公司工作。 “经济前景并不确定。”</p><p>即使消费者价格开始再次回升，中国工厂主和出口商也可能在一段时间内与定价权作斗争，从而侵蚀他们的利润率，并损害他们扩大生产或雇用更多工人的意愿。</p><p>尽管 7 月份生产者价格通缩有所缓解，但 4.4% 的降幅仍低于《华尔街日报》调查的经济学家预期的 4.1%。</p><p>疫情期间，中国许多工厂提高产量，以适应​​海外订单的激增。现在，随着西方需求的衰退，汽车、消费品和其他产品的生产商面临库存过剩的困境，迫使许多公司大幅降价以减少库存。</p><p>一家总部位于中国南方城市深圳的机器人吸尘器制造商正寻求扩大海外销量，部分原因是国内竞争对手提供更便宜的选择，而消费者需求复苏缓慢削弱了国内销售，公司高管表示。</p><p>中国决策者面临的最终挑战是如何防止价格下跌导致产量减少、工资下降和需求抑制的自我强化螺旋。</p><p>经济学家预计中国央行将在未来几个月进一步降低利率，但许多人对仅靠此类举措能否消除通缩压力持怀疑态度。</p><p>这是因为<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-stimulus-pivot-is-prompted-by-fears-slowing-growth-could-worsen-5d35d34?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">企业和家庭的信心恢复缓慢</a>，导致他们增加投资和支出的意愿有限。 BCA Research 首席新兴市场策略师阿瑟·布达吉安 (Arthur Budaghyan) 表示，这样的环境使得温和的刺激措施基本上无效。</p><p> “中国政府必须采取一些非常大的行动来应对通货紧缩，”他说。 “我认为他们做得还不够。”</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——北京的 Grace Zhu 和晓晓对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给谢一凡<a href="mailto:stella.xie@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">stella.xie@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 09:21:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-slips-into-deflation-in-warning-sign-for-world-economy-bbefb179</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-slips-into-deflation-in-warning-sign-for-world-economy-bbefb179<author><![CDATA[Stella Yifan Xie]]></author><category>原生金属</category><category>黑色金属</category><category>基本材料/资源</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>通货膨胀数字/价格指数</category><category>货币政策</category><category>利率</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>消费者价格指数</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>疫情/流行病</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>通货膨胀数字</category><category>价格指数</category><category>货币政策</category><category>利率</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>消费者价格指数</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>爆发</category><category>流行病</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>原生金属</category><category>黑色金属</category><category>基础材料</category><category>资源</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[China Slips Into Deflation in Warning Sign for Global Economy]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>取消 Covid-19 大流行限制后，消费者价格出现了不寻常的下跌，而不是飙升<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001121031"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
